# DB Ferry Project Context

- This is a plain static website with PWAs, not a Node/Vite/React build.
- The root app is the DB Ferry PWA.
- Additional utility PWAs live under `utilities/`, including `reciprocity-timer`, `recipe-book`, and `kcrw-tracklists`.
- The public static app is published from `main` to GitHub Pages by `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`.
- Firebase-backed utilities also deploy to Firebase Hosting project `fb-personal-utilities`.
- The live project URL is `https://fb2.github.io/db-schedule-pwa/`.
- The GitHub repository is `https://github.com/fb2/db-schedule-pwa`.

## Maintenance Workflow

- For normal static changes, edit files locally, test with `python3 -m http.server 5173`, commit to git, and push `main`.
- A push to `main` automatically triggers the GitHub Pages deployment workflow.
- For DB-backed utilities, also deploy Firebase Hosting with `npx firebase-tools deploy --only hosting`.
- For Firestore rule changes, deploy rules with `npx firebase-tools deploy --only firestore:rules`.
- Do not create a separate deployment branch unless the user explicitly asks to change the Pages architecture.
- When the user asks to save completed changes, use git commit and push unless they ask otherwise.

## Static Site Files

- `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` stages the static tree that is uploaded to Pages.
- New public files under the project root or `utilities/` are deployed automatically by the workflow's `rsync`.
- If the new file should work offline, add it to the relevant service worker `ASSETS` list.
- Each installable utility PWA should have its own `icon.svg` and manifest icon, not inherit the root DB Ferry icon.
- When changing a utility app shell, bump its service worker `CACHE_NAME` and script/style query strings to force installed PWAs to refresh.
- Keep asset paths relative, such as `./app.js`, because the app is hosted under `/db-schedule-pwa/`.

## Key Files

- `schedules.js`: ferry route data, public holidays, source links.
- `app.js`: browser app logic and rendering.
- `sw.js`: service worker and offline cache. Bump `CACHE_NAME` when forcing installed PWAs to refresh cached assets.
- `manifest.webmanifest`: installable PWA metadata and scope.
- `GITHUB_PAGES_MAINTENANCE.md`: human-readable maintenance and deployment guide.
